    "created_at": "2016-08-04T17:05:53Z",
    "updated_at": "2016-08-04T17:05:53Z",
    "body": "Notice that the buttons in the top right, have the cursor correct on the bottom portion only. Once the mouse moves into the upper half, the cursor reverts back to the default cursor. There's nothing in the CSS that enforces this behaviour, and i've confirmed this by checking in both Firefox and Chrome.\n"
