    "created_at": "2016-08-04T23:31:32Z",
    "updated_at": "2016-08-04T23:31:32Z",
    "body": "OK so I fixed your CSS so the drag region is actually correct (the button shouldn't be drag region)\n\n``` css\n.window_frame {\n    display: flex;\n    justify-content: space-between;\n\n    background: #0778CB;\n    color: white;\n}\n\n.window_frame .window_title {\n  padding: 10px 12px;\n  flex: 1;\n  -webkit-app-region: drag;\n}\n\n.window_frame .window_controls {\n  padding: 10px 12px;\n}\n\n.window_frame .window_controls span {\n    position: relative;\n    cursor: pointer;\n    top: 2px;\n    display: inline-block;\n}\n```\n\nHowever the bug is still present (but more obvious what it appears to be).\n\n@zcbenz It looks like the hidden frame border is \"still there\" just hidden and therefore adjusts the cursor.  Interestingly click events are still fired through it.  This appears to be a macOS specific frameless window bug.\n"
  },
